Step 2: Recognize the role of continuation strategies in the definition of subgame perfect equilibrium (SPE). For a strategy profile σ to be an SPE, it must be optimal for all players at every stage of the game, given the history of play up to that point. This means that for each t ≥ 1 and each history (x^(t-1), y^(t-1)), the continuation strategy σ|_(x^(t-1), y^(t-1)) must also be an equilibrium.
