Step 4: Ensure no profitable deviation exists. For σ to be an SPE, the government should not have an incentive to deviate from its continuation strategy σ|_(x^t, y^t) at any point in time. This implies that the value of following the continuation strategy must be at least as high as the value of any alternative strategy starting from the same history (x^t, y^t)."
